SUGOCA (スゴカ, Sugoka) is a Japanese rechargeable contactless smart card ticketing system for public transport in Fukuoka Prefecture and the surrounding areas.
SUGOCA will be introduced from spring 2009 in 144 stations of Fukuoka-Kitakyūshū area, mainly in Fukuoka Prefecture.
The three cards in Fukuoka and Suica, a card already used in Greater Tokyo Area by East Japan Railway Company (JR East), will have integrated services from spring 2010.
